-- Cerberus to buy United Rentals for $4 bln: report
-- 
-- Mon Jul 23, 2007 5:42am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/07/23/us-unitedrentals-cerberus-wsj-idUSL236284620070723

 

 LONDON  (Reuters) - Cerberus Capital Management is near a $4 billion deal to buy United Rentals Inc. ( URI.N ), the largest equipment rental company by fleet size, for $34.50 a share, the Wall Street Journal reported on Monday. 

 United Rentals said in April it was seeking a buyer and hired UBS and Credit Suisse to advise it. Its shares closed on Friday at $32.37.